result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Rosario G De Luna was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Rosario G De Luna was found guilty of Carry Concealed Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.23(2).
  • Rosario G De Luna was found guilty of Possession of Cocaine/Coca, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(c).

records.addlTxt:
AS TO COUNT 1:
Court ordered defendant to serve 60 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 60 days time served.  Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of $350.00 plus all mandatory costs, penalties, surcharges, and $50.00 ignition interlock surcharge, cash bail to apply due by 12/5/16 or entry of a civil judgment. Sentence to commence forthwith.  Court ordered AODA assessment and Driver's Safety Plan.  Defendant to cooperate with any treatment recommended.  Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for a period of 15 months.    Court orders defendant restricted to operation of vehicles equipped with an ignition interlock device for 15 months to commence upon eligibility to reinstate license.  

AS TO COUNT 4:
The Court ordered defendant to serve 90 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 59 days time served, STRAIGHT TIME.  

Court ordered NO court costs or fees, as they would cause an undue financial burden to the defendant. Sentence to commence FORTHWITH.

AS TO COUNT 5:
The Court ordered defendant to serve 30 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 0 days time served, STRAIGHT TIME.  

Court ordered NO court costs or fees, as they would cause an undue financial burden to the defendant. Sentence to commence FORTHWITH.

Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the criminal complaint and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.
